  "prompt": "How can you add money to a debit card from another card?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to add money to a debit card from another card:\n\n1. Bank Transfer\n- Transfer funds between linked bank accounts\n- Can be done online or through mobile banking app\n- Usually free if accounts are at the same bank\n\n2. Cash App or Venmo\n- Link both cards\n- Transfer money between cards\n- Typically instant transfer with small fee\n\n3. PayPal\n- Link multiple cards\n- Transfer funds between accounts\n- Some transfers are free, others have small fees\n\n4. Western Union\n- Transfer money online or in-person\n- Can load funds to prepaid debit cards\n- May charge transaction fees\n\n5. Money Transfer Services\n- Services like MoneyGram\n- Can transfer funds between cards\n- Usually involves fees\n\n6. Reload Prepaid Cards\n- Some prepaid cards allow loading from other cards\n- Can often do this online or at retail locations\n\n7. Direct Deposit\n- Have funds from another account deposited directly\n- Typically free and fastest method\n\n8. Wire Transfer\n- Bank-to-bank transfer\n- Often used for larger amounts\n- Usually involves fees\n\nChoose the method most convenient and cost-effective for your specific situation.",
